[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_mfjca")
log_title = "Intro to Thoth Observatory "
log_content = "Welcome to Thoth Observatory, as the current steward of this station you are entitled to certain information pertaining to this installation. These log files are intended to provide you with information, some of which the machine intelligence of this station may not feel is required to share. Starting with the basics, Thoth Observatory is a deep space research facility with a mass of roughly 1200 Metric Tons. The vast majority of this weight is comes from the Titanocarbon superstructure which the station is built on top of; the rest of the mass is split between power, life support, observational, and data processing systems. The station is designed to be crewed by only one individual at a time; there are many reasons for this but primarily it is a spatial limitation. Providing ample habitation for more than one crew member along with all other systems required for the station to function properly would not be possible under the constraints Thoth must operate within; these exact constraints will be elaborated on more thouroughly in future logs. 

This singular crew member is referred to as the steward of the station, and their primary task is to maintain the station and operate the equipment required to gather data. The stations automated systems will collate this information and perform analysis on it; they also can manage a significant portion of the maitanence required to keep the station functional. All this being considered, it should come as no suprise that the role of the steward is equal parts custodian as it is researcher; it requires a unique skillset encompassing astrophysics, computer science, and mechanical engineering, as such very few people are qualified to perform this task. Yet another complication is that by law stewards are required to rotate out of their positions every 2 solar weeks this is due to the mental strain induced by isolation and the at times crushing workload; it is not an easy job. 

Despite its difficulties this is quite possibly one of the most important jobs mankind has to offer, as the success of this mission bears so much import to the survival of our species. The investment of nearly 5 trillion dollars, the 5 year construction effort, the injuries and casualties sustained during the aformentioned construction, and the complete mental degredation of some of the first stewards assigned to Thoth, all of it and more would be a worthwhile cost to pay if this project is a success, and it has to be a success. There are no other options, aside from somehow being able to observe a naked singularity there are no other viable research paths to FTL communication, all other conceivable alternatives have been exhausted, the miracle that is Sejanus Singularity is the only path forward. "
is_locked = false
